<title type="html"><![CDATA[Nestopia or Nintendulator, Do Either emulate Bus Conflicts?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4246&amp;p=35185#p35185"><![CDATA[
I don't think any emulator will crash on a bus conflict so I would go about this by using FCEUXDSP for the conditional breakpoint feature. First break on any write, and note every address used, then put conditional breakpoints for A, X and Y != $address for each of the addresses.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Tue Jul 22, 2008 9:26 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
